  <entry>
    <id>tag:github.com,2008:Grit::Commit/53eb7667dd25f53fbf0d65e28370b32d90ab9448</id>
    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/commit/53eb7667dd25f53fbf0d65e28370b32d90ab9448"/>
    <title>
        New datasets update plugin extensions
    </title>
    <updated>2016-06-10T22:17:48Z</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/3874900?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>simonbrunel</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/simonbrunel</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;pre style=&#39;white-space:pre-wrap;width:81ex&#39;&gt;New datasets update plugin extensions

Add `beforeDatasetsUpdate` and `afterDatasetsUpdate` plugin notifications during the chart update. Plugins are able to cancel the datasets update by explicitly returning false to `beforeDatasetsUpdate`. For consistency, rename `(before|after)DatasetDraw` to `(before|after)DatasetsDraw`.&lt;/pre&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>tag:github.com,2008:Grit::Commit/dfdbd4465c6d35760aca60e7ff9bc58b62ac7cb9</id>
    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/commit/dfdbd4465c6d35760aca60e7ff9bc58b62ac7cb9"/>
    <title>
        Allow to register/unregister an array of plugins
    </title>
    <updated>2016-06-10T22:17:44Z</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/3874900?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>simonbrunel</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/simonbrunel</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;pre style=&#39;white-space:pre-wrap;width:81ex&#39;&gt;Allow to register/unregister an array of plugins

The plugins service now accepts an array of plugin instances to register or unregister (for consistency, renamed `Chart.plugins.remove` to `unregister`). Also added a few methods to manipulate registered plugins, such as `count`, `getAll` and `clear` (mainly used by our unit tests).&lt;/pre&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>tag:github.com,2008:Grit::Commit/a55c17d73fa7bfa9e2780fce3ea9a7770a11d8d3</id>
    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/commit/a55c17d73fa7bfa9e2780fce3ea9a7770a11d8d3"/>
    <title>
        Enhance plugin notification system
    </title>
    <updated>2016-06-10T20:26:55Z</updated>
    <media:thumbnail height="30" width="30" url="https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/3874900?s=30&amp;v=4"/>
    <author>
      <name>simonbrunel</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/simonbrunel</uri>
    </author>
    <content type="html">
      &lt;pre style=&#39;white-space:pre-wrap;width:81ex&#39;&gt;Enhance plugin notification system

Change the plugin notification behavior: this method now returns false as soon as a plugin *explicitly* returns false, else returns true. Also, plugins are now called in their own scope (so remove the never used `scope` parameter).&lt;/pre&gt;
    </content>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>tag:github.com,2008:Grit::Commit/7a419af4c2a9a4190fbe2ef550e20d38505cd648</id>
    <link type="text/html" rel="alternate" href="https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js/commit/7a419af4c2a9a4190fbe2ef550e20d38505cd648"/>
    <title>
